# Architecture

Full architecture spec: [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](../../docs/ARCHITECTURE.md). Read it before crossing system boundaries.

## Principles

- Modular systems, low coupling, high cohesion.
- Data-driven design - values live in Resources, not code.
- Composition over inheritance. Inheritance only for true "is-a" relationships.
- Single Responsibility Principle for every class and system.
- Clean separation between gameplay, UI, and data.

## System Boundaries

- Every major feature (Combat, Inventory, Equipment, Skills, Stats, Crafting, Saving, NPCs, Quests, UI, Audio) is isolated.
- Each system exposes a clean, documented API.
- No system directly manipulates another system's internal data.
- No circular dependencies. If two systems become tightly coupled, recommend a better architecture before implementing.

## Managers

Managers coordinate systems. They do NOT contain gameplay logic. Each manager has one responsibility.

- Good: `EnemyManager`, `ProjectileManager`, `SaveManager`, `AudioManager`, `UIManager`.
- Bad: `GameManager` that owns everything.

## Communication

- Prefer direct calls when ownership is obvious.
- Use signals only when they improve decoupling. Do not replace every function call with a signal.
- UI displays game state; UI does not own game state.

## Before Implementing

Always consult [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](../../docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) and the matching `docs/systems/<name>.md`. If the change does not fit the existing architecture, stop and ask.
